FitImage is an independent tool. It does NOT include or redistribute the source
code of Google's Squoosh; Squoosh is mentioned only as inspiration.

FitImage depends on the following at runtime (installed via npm, not vendored
into this repository):

  - sharp           Apache-2.0      https://github.com/lovell/sharp
      bundles libvips — LGPL-3.0-or-later (as distributed by the prebuilt
      @img/sharp-libvips-* packages) — and the codecs below.
  - commander       MIT             https://github.com/tj/commander.js

Codec licensing of the paths FitImage actually uses (via sharp/libvips):

  - JPEG : mozjpeg / libjpeg-turbo   BSD-3-Clause / IJG (permissive)
  - PNG  : zlib / libpng             zlib / libpng license (permissive)
  - WebP : libwebp                   BSD-3-Clause (permissive)

FitImage deliberately does NOT use sharp's `png({ palette: true })` option,
which would pull in libimagequant (GPL). All code paths used by FitImage are
therefore under permissive (BSD/zlib/MIT/Apache/LGPL) terms compatible with the
MIT license of this project.

Because these libraries are consumed as npm dependencies (downloaded by the end
user at install time) and are not redistributed within this repository, no
additional redistribution obligations are imposed by this project.

The libvips library (LGPL) is used via sharp as a dynamically loaded native
addon and may be replaced by the user with a compatible build, in accordance
with the terms of the LGPL.
